        <h3>Data Protection</h3>
        Protection of your data is important for help.today. There are mainly two sets of data we are receiving from you. Your account and registration information A) and information which results from the usage of the app B). The German version above has precedence.
        <h4>A) Account and registration data</h4>
        The installation process does not require you to enter personal data. However, to use all features of the app, we need to identify you by means of a confirmed email address. help.today stores your email address on the server after you entered it in the app and clicked on the confirmation mail. help.today does not give away or sell your account and registration information. help.today uses this information only to identify you at the start of the app and for merging accounts from different mobile phones. help.today may use the email address to send you information about the app. For identification by other users, you can set a user nickname. help.today publishes your nickname in relation to your posted Spots.
        
        For the use of the web shop and for merging your accounts from different mobile devices, help.today requires you to enter a password. help.today stores this password on the server.
        
        For improvement of your user experience, the registration process sends information about your mobile phone (OS version and language setting) to the server. The app uses a unique key to calculate a signature for your phone. help.today stores this key on the server. The key is constructed such that it is not possible to identify your phone based on this key after uninstalling the help.today App.
        
        B) Data from usage of the help.today App
        
